data.text:
Former Disney Star Anna Maria Perez de Tagle married her partner Scott Kline Jr. on Saturday. According to ABS-CBN News, the wedding was held in downtown Los Angeles at the Cathedral of Our Lady of the Angels.

Perez de Tagle previously appeared on Disney’s Hannah Montana and Camp Rock. Kline is a half-Filipino engineer. The couple met about two years ago after being set up by Perez de Tagle’s cousin.

According to GMA news, the couple got engaged last November 11. Close family and friends were in attendance at the wedding.

Perez de Tagle’s has acted in a few projects these past few years. In 2018, she appeared in an episode of Charmed. She is also set to appear in a 2019 film called The Message. She says that her husband is supportive of her career.
